entry.longSummary:
WYSIWYG .NET editor is an HTML editor that attempt to display the web page as it will show on the browser. It's a visual editor, and you don’t manipulate the code directly.

FEATURES:
1) Minimalist;
2) Open Source;
2) Browser supported: All;
4) Easy to install: Only one file (WYSIWYG.vb or WYSIWYG.cs);
5) Fluid and responsive;
6) Lightweight code: 5 KB;
7) Easy to implement in your .NET web; application: You need to add only one line of code
